  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed but all credibility factor gaps remain. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 factors not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5). Decision: Not accepted. NOTE: A Monte Carlo UQ campaign covering inlet velocity, fluid viscosity, and power-law hemolysis model coefficients was conducted across all five operating points; results are summarised in the validation report. Structured sensitivity analysis linkage is handled through the UQ campaign documentation referenced in wasDerivedFrom.",
